22/05/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Doctors at the Gulhane Military Medical Academy in Ankara said on Sunday (21 May) that they have decided to keep former Turkish Prime Minister Bulent Ecevit in a coma, to prevent further swelling in his brain. 
Ecevit, 81, underwent emergency surgery after suffering a stroke late Thursday. 
His condition is described as critical but stable. 
(Turks.US - 21/05/06)
